{"type":"message","id":"45f0e0e6","parentId":"a1d0d7ed","timestamp":"2026-02-19T18:07:01.443Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Constructing the Knowledge Base**\n\nI've just finished creating the `src/knowledge_base/history` folder. My next step is to begin populating the knowledge file at `src/knowledge_base/HFT_patterns.md`, as the \"Harper's Vault\" persona suggested. I'll be focusing on implementing zero-copy techniques, an event-driven architecture using Tokio's `mpsc`, and adaptive limiting strategies utilizing `X-RateLimit`.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"### 3. 🛡️ Harper's Vault (Knowledge Writing)\n\n> **[Harper]**: Writing high-frequency trading patterns to the vault...\n\nI will create `src/knowledge_base/HFT_patterns.md` with the critical architecture points.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771524421439_16","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# High-Frequency Trading (HFT) Patterns\n\n1. **Zero-Copy Serialization**\n   - Utilizing Rust's `serde` for direct memory mapping during JSON parsing.\n   - Eliminates redundant allocations for market data payloads.\n\n2. **Event-Driven Architecture**\n   - Built on `tokio::sync::mpsc` channels for non-blocking message passing.\n   - Decouples websocket ingestion from strategy execution loops.\n\n3. **Adaptive Rate Limiting**\n   - Dynamic throttle adjustment based on exchange `X-RateLimit` headers.\n   - Prevents IP bans during volatility spikes while maximizing throughput.\n","file_path":"src/knowledge_base/HFT_patterns.md"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4922,"output":303,"cacheRead":4464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5225,"cost":{"input":0.009844,"output":0.003636,"cacheRead":0.0008928000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014372800000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771524393421}}
